// Infect = a static ability [CR#702.90a] with two damage-result rewrites
// ([CR#120.3b,120.3d]), both SOURCE-keyed (`by: Ref(This)`, "damage dealt BY
// this"):
//   - to a CREATURE ([CR#702.90c]): not marked — instead that many -1/-1
//     counters ([CR#122.1a]) on the creature. Same shape as wither.
//   - to a PLAYER ([CR#702.90b]): no life loss — instead that many poison
//     counters ([CR#122.1f]) for that player. Ten poison = that player loses
//     ([CR#704.5c]).
//
// Modeled as ONE static ability holding TWO `Replacement` effects, branched by
// the `on` filter (`Type(Creature)` vs `Kind(Player)`) — the cleanest
// representable form: each branch is an independent replacement the registry
// gathers and the body's recipient binding differs (a creature recipient binds
// as `EventObject`; a player recipient — the proxy is zoneless, no LKI snapshot
// — binds as `EventActor`). `ThatMuch` ([CR#107.3], "that many") is the damage
// amount the replaced event carried; `This` stays the infect source. Multiple
// infect instances are redundant ([CR#702.90f]) — the lineage set ([CR#614.5])
// stops a second copy from applying twice to one event.
KeywordAbility(
    name: "Infect",
    template: "infect",
    abilities: [Static(effects: [
        // [CR#702.90c]: damage to a creature → -1/-1 counters.
        Replacement(Instead(
            would: Performed(verb: "DealDamage", by: Ref(This), on: Type(Creature)),
            instead: PutCounters(EventObject, M1M1Counter, ThatMuch),
        )),
        // [CR#702.90b]: damage to a player → poison counters.
        Replacement(Instead(
            would: Performed(verb: "DealDamage", by: Ref(This), on: Kind(Player)),
            instead: PutCounters(EventActor, Poison, ThatMuch),
        )),
    ])],
)
